        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(center)">Private</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>Dec 6. 1852</date> <placeName>New York</placeName></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev Dr Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In your note to me in answer<lb/> to a complaining one of mine respecting<lb/> the call of <persName>Marcussohn</persName>. You promised<lb/> to give room in your Paper &#38;<lb/> any reply I might have to make</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">As I have no knowledge of the<lb/> case in its origin only through correspondence<lb/> I shall let correspondents reply to<lb/> <persName>Mr <sic>Marcussohns</sic></persName> letter of <date>Sept 16<lb/> 1852</date> in the Occident. I have an addition<lb/>al letter upon the same subject by<lb/> <persName>Rev Mr Davis</persName> who wrote the letter<lb/> respecting his &#40;<persName>Mr M</persName>&#41; conversion<lb/> in Jewish Chronicle <date>Aug.</date> No.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">By inserting <persName>Rev C. D. Oliver&#39;s</persName> letter<lb/> here enclosed&#44; you will do justice to the<lb/> clergymen of <placeName>Montgomery Ala.</placeName> who<lb/> supposed <persName>Mr Marcussohn</persName> sincere<lb/> in his professions. I would beg you<lb/> also to insert the few remarks I have<lb/> sent you enclosed&#44; which may<lb/> serve to show how far <persName>Mr M.</persName> carried<lb/> the deception either of himself or of others</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">Yours with great respect</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">E R McGregor</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
